gwt.material.design.client.data

Class AbstractDataView<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gwt.material.design.client.data.AbstractDataView<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.gwt.event.shared.HasHandlers, com.google.gwt.view.client.HasKeyProvider<T>, com.google.gwt.view.client.HasRows, DataView<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InfiniteDataView, StandardDataView

    public abstract class AbstractDataView<T>
extends Object
implements DataView<T>
    Abstract DataView handles the creation, preparation and UI logic for the table rows and subheaders (if enabled). All of the basic table rendering is handled.
    Author:
    Ben Dol

      • renderRows

        protected void renderRows(Components<RowComponent<T>> rows)
        Compile list of RowComponent's and invoke a render. Controls the building of category components and custom components. Which then render(Components) is invoked to perform DOM render. Rows which are already rendered are reprocessed based on their equals method. If the data is equal to the row in the same index it use the existing row.
        Parameters:
        rows - list of rows to be rendered against the existing rows.
